title: David Murphy Hommers in Mets#039; Game 2 Victory
text:
Get Sports Alerts 
20 Oct 2015 07:30 AM EST 
The Chicago Cubs were defeated by the New York Mets 4-1 to take a strong 2-0 National League Championship Series lead at Citi Field. David Wright's struggle with the bat ended in this game while Mets manager Terry Collins marvels over the slugging performance of David Murphy. However, Cubs skipper Joe Maddon remains confident his team can turn the series around.
